race.comment: FIFTYFIVECHEVY (10) led for home but tanked soon after and dropped out last start over the Randwick mile. Steps up in distance today - a bit less pressure may be the key. Capable on his day and a quick return to form at good odds is on the cards. KENMARE BAY (5) came from last to get up and score an impressive win over 1550m at Canterbury last time out. Still has plenty of room to improve at just the third run of the prep so stick with him. IT'S A WONDER (4) settled a fair way back then really went through her gears nicely to get up for third in the Group 3 Belle Of The Turf over 1600m at Gosford recently. Not proven at nine furlongs but looks ready for the challenge. ASSOCIATE (3) has won two on the trot, the latest a gap job in open company over the mile at Wagga. Won't have any trouble negotiating this longer trip. Deserves this chance in town. CLIMB THE LADDER (14) has been finding the line well and today's longer journey looks ideal.
